author: Trumbull Times
title: Cross country: CHS girls sweep field, boys second
text:
By Trumbull Times on October 7, 2015 in High School Sports , Sports Features · 0 Comments 
The Christian Heritage School of Trumbull girls cross country team pulled out the win over Wooster, Chase, Watkinson and Forman at the Housatonic Valley Athletic League Invitational on Wednesday. 
The top five finishers for CHS were Claire Parrish, Lydia Kellogg, Abby Slater, Laura Bruening and Emily Fererria. 
The boys team finished second in the seven-team field, losing narrowly to Watkinson, and defeating Forman, South Kent, Chase Collegiate, Harvey School and Wooster. 
The top five boys finishers were Mitchell Modarelli, Matt Bruening, Connor Hartman, Will Rojas and Zach Zysk. Related posts:
